Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide
chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn
halfway through.

Meanwhile, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{70%grams}.

In a #small bowl{}, mix together the @tomato puree{60%grams} and
@water{1%tbsp}. Season with salt and pepper.

Pop the @plain naans{2} onto a large baking tray. Divide the tomato sauce
between them and spread with the back of a #spoon{}, leaving a 1cm border.

Top with the @chorizo slices{50%grams}, then sprinkle over the cheese.

When the chips have 10 mins left, bake your naanizzas on the middle shelf until
the cheese is golden and bubbling, ~{7-10%minutes}.

While everything's in the oven, in a #medium bowl{}, combine the
@cider vinegar{15%milliliters}, @sugar{1%tsp} and @olive oil{1%tbsp}. Season with
salt and pepper.

Just before everything's ready, toss the @baby leaf mix{50%grams} through the
dressing.

Share the naanizzas between your plates and drizzle over the @honey{15%grams}.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, put the sachet in a bowl of hot water for
> ~{1%minute} to loosen.

Serve the salad and chips alongside with the @tomato ketchup{2%tbsp} for
dipping. Enjoy!